description.narrative: Increased the number of children receiving care in the framework of the Baby Friendly Hospital Initiative (IHAN), including quality complementary feeding in public maternal and child health centers prioritized, which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, pregnant women and new-borns, children and adolescents have equitable access to essential lifesaving health care services

description.narrative: TThe nutrition response focuses on providing access to nutrition services and programs through the provision of essential nutrition services for the prevention of acute malnutrition for children under 5 years of age, pregnant and lactating women and interventions for the treatment of acute malnutrition and underweight in pregnant women, specially focused on pregnant adolescents. Protocols for early detection and treatment of acute malnutrition were adapted to the context of COVID-19 situation, health and nutrition staff were trained in these adaptations for the prompt nutrition service delivery. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
